  "prompt": "What do they call it when you get beat on a big play and you act injured in football?",
  "response": "In football, when a player gets beaten on a big play and then appears to act injured to stop the play or disrupt the game, it is often referred to as \"flopping\" or \"acting.\" This tactic can be used to buy time, regroup, or influence the referee's decision, though it's generally considered unsportsmanlike conduct. In some contexts, it's also called \"embellishment\" or \"simulation.\"",
